  "datePublished": "2026-03-06",
  "description": "Mimicry is one of Roger Caillois\u0026rsquo;s four fundamental categories of play: play structured around becoming someone or something else — taking on a role, inhabiting a fiction, simulating a situation. Theater, role-playing games, children\u0026rsquo;s pretend play, cosplay, and simulation games all involve mimicry. The player temporarily sets aside their ordinary identity and operates as a fictional persona, and the interest comes not from competition or chance but from the experience of transformation itself — seeing through different eyes, making choices you wouldn\u0026rsquo;t otherwise make, inhabiting a world that doesn\u0026rsquo;t exist.\n",
  "name": "mimicry",
